# Keep type comparison docs current

**Rule:** After adding a type, trait method, adapter, conversion, proto message, or NATS topic that affects cross-backend comparisons, update `docs/BACKEND_TYPE_COMPARISON.md` in the same change when practical.

## When to update

| Change | Doc touch |
|--------|-----------|
| New `BrokerEngine` trait method | Comparative tables — per-adapter coverage |
| New adapter | Adapter columns / rows |
| New `*Position*` / `*Order*` type | Position/order tables + conversions |
| New proto / topic | Proto / messaging section |

## Quick consistency checks

```bash
rg "pub struct.*Position" agents/backend/crates --type rust
rg "async fn " agents/backend/crates/broker_engine/src/traits.rs
rg "From<.*> for|impl From" agents/backend/crates/common --type rust
```

**Parity:** Same policy as `.opencode/rules/keep-type-comparison-docs.md` (OpenCode).
